.SH NAME
GamepadButton \- GamepadButton
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]GamepadButton\f[B]\f[R] interface defines an individual
button of a gamepad or other controller, allowing access to the current
state of different types of buttons available on the control device.
.PP
A \f[CR]GamepadButton\f[R] object is returned by querying any value of
the array returned by the \f[CR]buttons\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]Gamepad\f[R] interface.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
.TP
\f[B]GamepadButton.pressed\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
A boolean value indicating whether the button is currently pressed
(\f[CR]true\f[R]) or unpressed (\f[CR]false\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]GamepadButton.touched\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
A boolean value indicating whether the button is currently touched
(\f[CR]true\f[R]) or not touched (\f[CR]false\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]GamepadButton.value\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
A double value used to represent the current state of analog buttons,
such as the triggers on many modern gamepads.
The values are normalized to the range 0.0 \(em1.0, with 0.0
representing a button that is not pressed, and 1.0 representing a button
that is fully pressed.
.SH EXAMPLE
The button values in the following example are stored as an array of
\f[CR]GamepadButton\f[R] objects.
This simple example checks to see if the \f[CR]GamepadButton.value\f[R]
of a button is greater than \f[CR]0\f[R], or if the
\f[CR]GamepadButton.pressed\f[R] property indicates the button has been
pressed.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]function\f[R] gameLoop() {
  \f[B]const\f[R] gp = navigator.getGamepads()[0];

  \f[B]if\f[R] (gp.buttons[0].value > 0 || gp.buttons[0].pressed) {
    b\-\-;
  } \f[B]else\f[R] \f[B]if\f[R] (gp.buttons[1].value > 0 || gp.buttons[1].pressed) {
    a++;
  } \f[B]else\f[R] \f[B]if\f[R] (gp.buttons[2].value > 0 || gp.buttons[2].pressed) {
    b++;
  } \f[B]else\f[R] \f[B]if\f[R] (gp.buttons[3].value > 0 || gp.buttons[3].pressed) {
    a\-\-;
  }

  ball.style.left = \(ga${a * 2}px\(ga; \f[I]// ball is a UI widget\f[R]
  ball.style.top = \(ga${b * 2}px\(ga;

  requestAnimationFrame(gameLoop);
}
.EE
